Privacy Policy

Protecting your privacy is important to us. We hope the following statement will help you understand how our app deals with the personal identifiable information ('PII') you may occasionally provide to us via Internet (the Google Play Platform).

Generally, we do not collect any PII from you when you download our Android applications. To be specific, we do not require the consumers to get registered before downloading the application, nor do we keep track of the consumers' visits of our application, we even don't have a Server to store such PII.

Information we collect
Cookies ( Webview browser cookies) - When you visit Forum service, we may send one or more cookies ? files with small amount of data that is commonly used an anonymous unique identifier ?to your mobile device that uniquely identifies your device and allows the application to help you log in faster and enhance your navigation through the Forum. You can reset your web browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. If you choose to refuse our cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of this Service.

Ads - Our app may uses Facebook as ads provider. Facebook uses cookies (as described above) to make it possible to analyze how users use Our Services, and show ads that are relevant to you. For more information, please check https://m.facebook.com/ads/ad_choices.

Analytics - We use third party analytics tool, Google Analytics, to help us measure traffic and usage trends for the service. Google Analytics collects information such as how often users visit our services, what pages they visit when they do so, and what other pages they use prior to coming to our services. We use the information get from Google Analytics only to improve our services.

Health Kit- You will also have an option to permit us to import health data into the App from third-party services such as Google Fit. Permitting us to access third party information can help you to maximize your App experience, and we will handle any such third-party information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.

Log file - The only situation we may get access to your PII is when you personally decide to email us your feedback or to provide us with a bug log report. The PII we may get from you in that situation are strictly limited to your name, email address, device information, location Information and your survey response only.

How we use your information
In above situation, we guarantee that your PII will only be used for conOTPting you and improving our services. We will never use such information (e.g. your name and email address) for any other purposes, such as to further market our products, or to disclose your personal information to a third party for commercial gains.

ConOTPt us
It should be noted that whether or not to send us your feedback or bug report is a completely voluntary initiative upon your own decision. If you have concern about your PII being misused, or if you want further information about our privacy policy and what it means, please feel free to email us at kem.beliadansukan@gmail.com, we will endeavor to provide clear answers to your questions in a timely manner.

January 11, 2020 (Saturday) - The Community Service Component has been successfully implemented at Kg Islamic Cemetery. River Bertam, Batang Kali on Saturday, January 11, 2020. \ n Attendance of freshmen during the 1/2020 session and about 125 staff members worked together to clear the cemetery from 7.30am. Among the voluntary activities carried out were packing in and out of the As Sajidin Mosque, collecting twigs and decaying branches, cleaning clams and wiping dried leaves around the area. \ nWe are here to help with this partnership The Mosque Committee has donated breakfast to the students of the IKBN Printers and the local community. \ N This program is the final slot in the IKBN Printer Session 1/2020 Session Week Program in the hope that students can foster a sense of cooperation and enhance their future volunteer work. \ N Provided by: Mrs. Azini Binti Ismail

SELAMAT DATANG PELAJAR BARU KE IKBN PERETAK BAGI SESI 1/2020

IKBN Peretak, 6 Januari 2020 (Isnin) – Hari Pendaftaran bagi pelajar-pelajar baru Sesi 1/2020 ILKBS telah diadakan pada 6 Januari 2020 (Isnin). Sebanyak 6 bidang SKM dan 1 Bidang Diploma telah ditawarkan oleh IKBN Peretak pada Sesi 1/2020 ini iaitu bagi bidang:
 1. Sijil Lanjutan Teknologi Terapi Kecantikan
2. Sijil Lanjutan Teknologi Perekaan Gaya Rambut
3. Sijil Lanjutan Teknologi Penyediaan Roti
 4. Sijil Lanjutan Teknologi Penyediaan Pastri
5. Sijil Lanjutan Teknologi Penyajian Makanan & Minuman
6. Sijil Lanjutan Teknologi Jahitan Pakaian Wanita
 7. Diploma Rekaan Fesyen
Pada tegaharinya telah diadakan sesi taklimat kepada ibu-bapa/penjaga pelajar baru oleh Pengarah IKBN Peretak sempena Pendaftaran pelajar baru Sesi pengambilan Januari, 2020.
 Selamat datang kepada semua pelajar baru ke IKBN Peretak bagi Sesi 1/2020. Semoga cita-citamu akan tercapai.
LAWATAN MENGEJUT DARIPADA KSU DAN TKSU STRATEGIK, KEMENTERIAN BELIA DAN SUKAN (KBS)

31 Disember 2019 (Selasa), IKBN Peretak – IKBN Peretak berbesar hati menerima lawatan mengejut daripada YBrs Dr. Waitchalla R.R Suppiah (KSU KBS) & Pn. Ramona binti Mohd. Razali (TKSU Strategik). KSU dan TKSU (S) sempat meluangkan masa melawat Dewan DAHA, butik dan bengkel projek inkubator Jabatan Tekstil, Perpustakaan, Pejabat Pentadbiran, kawasan chalet, kuarters dan pejabat AKBG.\n Beberapa isu yang telah dibangkitkan kepada Dr KSU & Pn.TKSU (S) adalah ketiadaan sistem pengudaraan dan pencahayaan yang baik di Dewan DAHA, masalah talian telefon dan Wifi serta sistem penggera kebakaran yang perlu dibaiki. Sesi lawatan bermula pada jam 10.00 pagi dan selesai sekitar jam 11.15 pagi.
